# Website Refresh Guardrails

- Do not change website copy, claims, names, dates, or links unless explicitly asked.
- Prioritize visual polish through layout, spacing, typography, color, imagery, and component styling.
- Preserve existing page structure and information hierarchy unless explicitly asked to restructure.
- Keep interactions restrained: no flashy motion, no parallax-heavy effects, no attention-grabbing loops.
- Favor subtle transitions only when they improve clarity.

## Content Safety

- Treat all text content as locked by default.
- If an edit requires text adjustment for technical reasons, pause and ask first.

## Delivery Style

- Make focused, reversible changes.
- Prefer shared style/token updates over one-off component hacks.
